organization.title: Cambridgeshire Insight
organization.description: The Cambridgeshire Insight Partnership is made up of public, health and community bodies to provide a shared research knowledge base for the Cambridgeshire area. It allows users an easy way to access and share data, information and research for deeper insights about their local area. See more at https://cambridgeshireinsight.org.uk

result.title: Cambridgeshire Adult Learning Fund (CALF) 2010 - 2014 Breakdown of Course Categories

resources.description:
Total number of registered learners on a Cambridgeshire Adult Learning Fund (CALF) course who studied a Functional Skills course. This includes English, Literacy, Maths and Finance. These are based on the location of the course venue, between the academic years of 2010/2011 to 2014/2015.
Please note: All low cell counts of below 5, have all been rounded up and replaced with a 5. This prevents any breaches of the Data Protection Act 1998.
